        July 8, 2009<br><br>JMJ / MMM     090708  Wednesday<br>I’d like to add something important to this topic .. <u>and then I’ll continue in topic “Divinization, Theosis..</u>”<br><br>The two major kinds of grace are <font color="Blue">sanctifying or habitual grace</font> .. and <font color="blue">actual grace</font>.<br><br>It is God’s purpose in creating us that we creatures, we finite beings, truly and really SHARE WITH GOD IN LIVING THE DIVINE LIFE in Jesus in the Trinity.  If we were to become perfect human beings -- and that’s all -- we would have totally missed what God has planned for us and given us in Jesus Christ.  We would have “lost” our souls.<br><br><font color="blue"><b>Sanctifying Grace</b> (also called Habitual Grace because after Baptism it resides in our souls permanently unless we lose it by mortal sin) .. Sanctifying Grace causes, effects, in us A PERMANENT <i>CHANGE</i> IN OUR <i>NATURE</i>.  Instead of continuing as mere human beings, creatures of God, we are made by God true and REAL sons and daughters of God.  God has done this through His Son Jesus Christ.  It’s like taking one ant and making the ant to be the greatest human composer and pianist ever to be.</font>  It's even more than that.  See especially <b>CCC</b> 1997 through 2000.<br><br>Over the course of the centuries the Church (founded by Christ) in the East has kept this emphasis.  We find it expressed especially in their great celebration of the Transfiguration.  But in the Church in the West (that’s we, Latin) we have  neglected to give it it’s <i>central</i> position in favor of emphasis on avoiding sin and obeying the commandments.<br><br><font color="blue"><b>Actual Graces</b></font> are God’s free gift to each of us in our free choice ACTions.  These graces are not permanent but are with us as we need them.  These also can be of several kinds.<br><br>It has been mentioned in our posts that this idea of <font color="Red">SHARING IN GOD’S VERY DIVINE LIFE</font> is needing to be further developed.  I’d like to continue sharing this in another topic already begun in the forums, <i>Divinization, Theosis</i>.<br>May Holy Spirit enter us and possess us .. in Jesus Christ Trinity!      John (JohnJFarren)</span>
